{
  "eval_set_id": "routing_evalset",
  "name": "Simple Router \u2014 Routing Accuracy & Multi-turn Flows",
  "description": "Covers single-domain routing, multi-domain orchestration, cross-turn state, follow-up bypass, static routing, and fallback handling.\n\nDesign note: tool_trajectory_avg_score compares on both name AND args (exact match per tool).\nTo keep assertions reliable across model runs, we only assert on tools whose args we can predict:\n  - get_conversation_context / signal_follow_up  \u2192 no user-visible args \u2192 args={} is exact\n  - get_invoice_details / note_invoice_id         \u2192 invoice_id is the user-supplied ID, predictable\n  - get_support_steps / invoice_agent_helper etc  \u2192 args contain free-text from the model, unpredictable\nFor routing assertions (which agent handled the request), intermediate_responses is the source of truth.\n\nStatic routing cases (static_route_*):\n  The before_model_callback may bypass the router LLM entirely for high-confidence messages.\n  From the eval perspective the routing outcome is identical \u2014 intermediate_responses still shows\n  which expert handled the request. These cases validate that static routing reaches the correct\n  expert and that the re-route guard releases cleanly on subsequent turns.",
  "eval_cases": [
    {
